com.samysadi.acs.user

Interface ThinClientVirtualMachine

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Entity, Notifier, Probed, RunnableEntity, VirtualMachine
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ThinClientVirtualMachineDefault

    public interface ThinClientVirtualMachine
extends VirtualMachine
    A thin client VM is different from regular VMs because you cannot allocate some resources types for it (virtual ram, virtual storage, processing units).
    If you try to allocate such resources you will get an UnsupportedOperationException.

    Also, a thin client VM user is always the same as the ThinClient's parent.
    If you try to set a user for a thin client VM, then the method call is ignored.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Samy Sadi , Belabbas Yagoubi

      • clone

        ThinClientVirtualMachine clone()
        Description copied from interface: VirtualMachine
        Creates a clone of current VM, and unsets any assigned resource on that clone (usable processing units, usable storages, usable network interfaces, virtual ram and virtual storage).

        The same user owns the cloned VM and it has the same SLA constraints.

        Other children entities are cloned just as specified by superclass clone method.
